.\engines\taxonomy\SPEC.md:708:**T-1 (Silent Text Corruption) → Taxonomy vector: serialization corruption during placement write.** The taxonomy engine writes the placed excerpt to disk as JSON. If the JSON serializer mishandles Arabic text (e.g., double-encoding UTF-8, stripping diacritics, normalizing Unicode forms), the `primary_text` in the placed file differs from the input. **Prevention:** (a) Post-write fidelity check in §5.1 — the engine re-reads the written file and compares `primary_text` byte-for-byte against the input. (b) The taxonomy engine never modifies `primary_text` — it is copied verbatim from the draft excerpt. (c) JSON serialization uses `ensure_ascii=False` to preserve Arabic characters without escape sequences. **Residual risk:** LOW — the post-write check catches any serialization corruption before the placement is committed.
